‚öñÔ∏è 1. Legal Clarification ‚Äî ‚ÄúIs This a Security?‚Äù

No. CivicVerse is not a security.

Under the U.S. Howey Test, a security requires:
	1.	An investment of money
	2.	In a common enterprise
	3.	With the expectation of profit
	4.	From the efforts of others

CivicVerse fails that test. Here‚Äôs why:
	‚Ä¢	No money is required to participate
	‚Ä¢	No common enterprise exists‚Äîonly open-source code
	‚Ä¢	No promise of profit is made
	‚Ä¢	No centralized team controls outcomes

Participation is voluntary. Outcomes are simulated. Profits are non-guaranteed. The system is open. No laws are broken.

